---

<Base
  title="Hair Restoration in Houston, Texas | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Hair Restoration in Houston, Texas at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Hair Restoration in Houston, Texas"
  headerImage="/img/hair-resto-hero.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/male-facelift-houston"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                                The skin and soft tissues of the face are prone to wrinkles and deflation with age. While everyone ages in their own way, we offer a male facelift for men looking to combat the effects of aging on their skin.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>


            <section class="mb-0 pb-240">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>          
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What are the benefits of a male facelift?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    The main benefit of a male facelift is the rejuvenated, younger look. At The Oaks Plastic Surgery, our plastic surgeons strive to utilize techniques that preserve the natural look of a patient’s face, avoiding excessive tightening or unnecessary steps that can lead to the very artificial or “frozen” look that are tell-tale signs that someone has had a facelift.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Often times people think of a facelift as a purely cosmetic procedure, and while technically speaking that’s true, the reason for seeking out a cosmetic procedure varies from person to person. From erasing wrinkles to recovering after significant weight loss, or just finding a personal look that you’re happy to see in the mirror every day, the emotional and psychological benefits of being comfortable with how you look are difficult to overstate. At TOPS, our surgeons take this into consideration and offer their experience and technical skill to help patients realize a self image that they’re truly comfortable with.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Procedures commonly paired with a male facelift:</h3>
                                <p>
                                    As we mentioned earlier, it’s not uncommon for patients to undergo a neck lift or a fat transfer to improve the results of their facelift. Other procedures that patients might consider are <a href="/blepharoplasty-surgery-houston">upper eyelid surgery</a> or <a href="/blepharoplasty-surgery-houston">lower eyelid surgery</a> (upper blepharoplasty or lower blepharoplasty),<a href="/houston-eyebrow-lift">brow lift</a>, and/or <a href="/houston-botox">botox</a>, <a href="/fillers-houston">fillers</a>, or <a href="/chemical-peel-houston">chemical peel</a>.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                   Leading up to and after your facelift procedure, developing a quality skin care routine will help fight the signs of aging and keep your newly structured skin clean and healthy. Having a great deal of experience in both the surgery and aftercare, TOPS surgeons and staff may be able to make recommendations or guide you in finding products that will help with both the healing process and ongoing skincare after your surgery.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Why choose TOPS Houston for your male facelift?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Rather than simply pinning back your skin and sending you on your way, TOPS Houston surgeons are dedicated to discussing and fully planning your male facelift. Not everyone is looking for the exact same thing, and our surgeons understand that.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    You’ll be working closely with your surgeon leading up to the procedure to ensure that both your primary surgery and any specific or additional aspects are handled exactly the way you intended. TOPS Houston will help you meet your specific and personal cosmetic goals.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Your Initial Male Facelift Consultation</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    As with all surgical procedures carried out at The Oaks Plastic Surgery, leading up to your male facelift, your surgeon will:
                                </p>                               
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Meet with you to discuss your particular goals for surgery</li>
                                    <li>Perform a thorough pre-op exam</li>
                                    <li>Develop an understanding of your state of health to better prep for an operation</li>
                                    <li>Discuss the benefits, risks, and various options associated with your upcoming surgery. </li>
                                    <li>Determine the various particulars of your operation, such as incision sites or additional procedures.</li>
                                    <li>Provide you with information and instruction about your procedure and the recovery process once it has been completed.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>

                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Male Facelift Recovery and Aftercare</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    Your aftercare and recovery time may vary depending on the number of procedures that you opted in for during your male facelift procedure. On average, by carefully following the aftercare instructions provided by TOPS Houston, patients can a recovery time of two to three weeks. Everyone heals at a different rate, but if you have concerns, you are always able to contact your surgeon after your procedure to ask questions or discuss any further aftercare.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Your TOPS surgeon will also contact you after surgery to ensure that your recovery process is proceeding smoothly, answering any questions or concerns you might have while providing follow up advice on your aftercare if necessary.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Are you looking for a fresh, rejuvenated face? TOPS Houston would love to help make that dream a reality. <a href="/contact-us">Contact us today</a> to get more information about a male facelift and other procedures!
                                </p>
                            </div>

                        </div>
                    </div>
